x4freetext: Some excitation functions of neutron induced reactions
at 180 keV for absolute cross section
Errors due to statistics, geometry, counting
efficiency and flux calibration included. Errors
The total error of the flux measurement was
about 4.5% which essentially comprises of the errors
in the counting efficiency of the stilbene crystal,
in the energy calibration curve for protons in stilbene
and in the estimation of edge-effects and multiple n-p
G.C. 4 Data sets added from EANDC(E)-57.
G.C., Error analysis changed and monitor
SD: Updated to new date formats,lower case.

flux measurement at 14.1 MeV only. Error in
flux calibration 4.5%. Cross sections at other
energy measured relative to the 14.1 MeV point.
